---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Crest from "../components/Crest.astro";
import PhotoFrame from "../components/PhotoFrame.astro";
import SectionHeading from "../components/SectionHeading.astro";
import { withBase } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Poopsie"
  description="In loving memory of Dennis “Poopsie” Burski — the always-smiling grandfather who won the very first tournament and gave the Poopsie Beanbag Invitational its name."
>
  <!-- Memorial header -->
  <section class="mem">
    <div class="wrap-narrow mem__inner">
      <Crest size={120} withText={false} animate />
      <p class="eyebrow mem__kicker">In loving memory</p>
      <h1 class="mem__name">Dennis “Poopsie” Burski</h1>
      <!-- TODO(content): confirm birth year for dates, e.g. "1943 – 2020". -->
      <p class="mem__dates stat-face">Grandpa · Champion · The reason we gather · — 2020</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="band-rule wrap-narrow" role="presentation"></div>

  <!-- Story -->
  <article class="wrap-narrow story">
    <p class="story__lead" data-reveal>
      Grandpa Burski was always a happy, smiling man who enjoyed nothing more
      than being around his family. He worked hard and played harder, and his
      whole mission was making sure everyone was smiling and laughing —
      especially the grandkids.
    </p>

    <PhotoFrame ratio="16 / 9" caption="TODO: a favorite photo of Grandpa Burski." />

    <SectionHeading eyebrow="Who he was" title="A grandpa in every crowd" />
    <p data-reveal>
      Along with Grandma Pat, he was at nearly every sporting event and school
      event the grandkids ever had. If a grandkid was playing, the Burskis were
      in the stands — a streak made possible, in no small part, by the legendary
      Christmas <strong>“GAS CARD!”</strong> gifts that kept everyone on the road
      and together.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="pull" data-reveal>
      He wanted everyone smiling — and he had a belly bump waiting for any
      grandkid who came close enough.
    </blockquote>

    <SectionHeading eyebrow="The name" title="Where “Poopsie” came from" />
    <div class="callout card-paper" data-reveal>
      <p>
        The nickname goes all the way back to his school days with Grandma Pat.
        Exactly how he earned it is a story still being pieced together —
      </p>
      <!-- TODO(content): replace with the real origin of the "Poopsie" nickname. -->
      <p class="callout__todo">
        <em>The family is still gathering the full story — check back soon.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

    <SectionHeading eyebrow="The competitor" title="First to win the Cup" />
    <div class="story__split">
      <div data-reveal>
        <p>
          Grandpa had a gift for bean bags and horseshoes, and he proved it
          right away: he <strong>won the very first tournament</strong>, back
          when it was still called the Agate Cup. He'd go on to win a few more
          over the years, with a rotating cast of partners — and Grandma Pat
          right beside him for the best of them.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a class="story__link" href={withBase("/champions")}>See his years in the Hall of Champions →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <PhotoFrame caption="TODO: Poopsie at the boards, or holding the Cup." />
    </div>

    <SectionHeading eyebrow="2020" title="Carrying the tradition forward" />
    <p data-reveal>
      Grandpa Burski passed away in 2020. To make sure the yearly tradition he
      loved could continue, the Agate Cup was renamed the
      <strong>Poopsie Beanbag Invitational</strong> in his honor. Every July 4th
      weekend since, the family has gathered at the lake to toss bags, talk
      trash, and celebrate the man who taught them how.
    </p>

    <div class="closing" data-reveal>
      <Crest size={80} withText={false} />
      <p class="closing__line">Still smiling over every toss.</p>
      <a class="btn" href={withBase("/gallery")}>Visit the gallery</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mem {
    text-align: center;
    padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .mem__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .mem__kicker {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .mem__name {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 3.6rem);
    margin: 0.35rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .mem__dates {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-faint);
  }

  .story {
    padding-block: 2.5rem 1rem;
  }
  .story > :global(p) {
    margin-block: 1.1rem;
  }
  .story__lead {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-lake-deep);
  }
  .story :global(.frame) {
    margin-block: 2rem;
  }
  .story :global(.sec-head) {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .pull {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-amber);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-agate);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .callout {
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
  }
  .callout p {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .callout__todo {
    color: var(--color-ink-faint);
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }
  .story__split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .story__split :global(.frame) {
    margin-block: 0;
  }
  .story__link {
    font-family: var(--font-accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-agate);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .story__link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .closing {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .closing__line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-lake-deep);
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .story__split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
